==English==

===Etymology===
Probably from {{etyl|non}} {{term|slyngja|lang=non}}, {{term|slyngva|lang=non||to hurl}}, from {{proto|Germanic|slingwanan|to worm, twist}} (compare Old English {{term|slingan|lang=ang||to wind, twist}}, German {{term|schlingen|lang=de||to swing, wind, twist}}, Danish {{term|slynge|lang=da}}), from {{proto|Indo-European|slenk|to turn, twist}} (compare Welsh {{term|llyngyr|lang=cy||worms, maggots}}, Lithuanian {{term|sliñkti|lang=lt||to crawl like a snake}}, Latvian {{term|slìkt|lang=lv||to sink}}).

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈslɪɳ/}}
* {{rhymes|ɪŋ}}

